The name of the user who initiated the image upgrade is contained in avctDsrTrapObjectUserName if available. An empty string is reported if a user name is not available. event.descr:
The result of a software image file upgrade. The result is for the main image file that contains all of the software components for the entire appliance. The result is contained in avctDsrTrapObjectImageFileUpgradeResult. The name of the user who originally started the image upgrade is contained in avctDsrTrapObjectUserName if available. An empty string is reported if a user name is not available. A user name will not be available if the image upgrade was started from the CLI port. The type of software image the upgrade result is for is contained in avctDsrTrapObjectTypeOfImage. The software image version the appliance is running is contained in avctDsrTrapObjectImageCurrentVersion. If the software image upgrade was successful then this version will match the version reported in avctDsrTrapObjectImageNewVersion. The name of the user who terminated or preempted the virtual media session is contained in avctDsrTrapObjectUserName if available. An empty string is reported if a user name is not available. A user name will not be available if the remote virtual media session was terminated or preempted from the OSCAR interface and OSCAR authentication is disabled. The name of the user who was terminated or preempted from the virtual media session is contained in avctDsrTrapObjectTargetUserName. The name of the server the user was connected to contained in avctDsrTrapObjectServerName. The input port number on the appliance that the virtual session was using is contained in avctDsrTrapObjectInputPort. The ID of the IQ Adaptor the virtual media session was using is contained in avctDsrTrapObjectIqAdaptorId. The cascade switch channel number the virtual media session was using is contained in avctDsrTrapObjectSwitchChannel. This value will be 0 if a switch channel was not being used for the virtual media session. The number of active sessions associated with this connection is contained in avctDsrTrapObjectActiveSessions. Supported by the following appliance types: DSR1030 DSR2030 DSR4030 DSR8030 DSR2035 DSR8035 DSR1031
